oc:kn_20040806 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding level of documentation for an experiment" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the Quick Test Brief for simple tests and the full Test Plan Template for complex tests. Overhead should match experiment scope." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Right-sizing documentation prevents process overhead from blocking velocity on simple tests while ensuring rigorous documentation for high-stakes experiments." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_27a88bbd a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing test measurement strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always define primary metrics, secondary metrics, AND guardrail metrics before running a test. Guardrail metrics protect against harmful side effects." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Guardrail metrics prevent implementing a change that improves one metric while silently degrading a critical business metric like revenue or load time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2902e53c a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When finalizing test design" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include segment analysis plan (mobile vs desktop, new vs returning, traffic source) and pre-define success/inconclusive/loser criteria before running the test." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Pre-defining criteria prevents confirmation bias and p-hacking. Segment analysis often reveals insights hidden in aggregate results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_55db809a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before launching any A/B test" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never skip the pre-launch checklist — especially tracking verification and QA across all variants." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Launching with broken tracking means collecting unusable data and wasting the entire test period. This is the most common and most costly A/B testing mistake." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f8b47eac a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any test plan or experiment brief" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every A/B test must have a documented hypothesis following the 'Because [observation], we believe [change] will cause [outcome] for [audience], measured by [metrics]' format." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A structured hypothesis ensures tests are evidence-driven rather than opinion-driven and makes the reasoning auditable post-test." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

